The paper deals with text classification, which is a common topic in natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the computer science sub-category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The use of deep reinforcement learning (RL) also suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of neural encoders, which are commonly used in deep learning (cs.DL) for NLP tasks. Finally, the paper deals with label hierarchies, which are often used in information retrieval (cs.IR) to organize and classify documents.
